    <section id="cpp">
      <h2 class="h3-visual">C and C++ Development Environment</h2>
      <ul>
        <li class="bullet">
          Essentials: Core development tools including build-essential, gdb,
          g++-multilib, and related packages. Install with:
          <div
            class="code-container"
            style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
          >
            <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
            <pre
              class="command-line"
              data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">sudo apt install build-essential lldb ninja-build clang gdb g++-multilib -y</code></pre>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="bullet">
          <a href="https://cmake.org/" class="url">CMake</a> and CMake GUI: Build
          system generator with GUI support for easier project configuration. Install
          with:
          <div
            class="code-container"
            style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
          >
            <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
            <pre
              class="command-line"
              data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">sudo apt install cmake cmake-qt-gui -y</code></pre>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="bullet">
          Package Managers:
          <ul>
            <li class="bullet">
              <a href="https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg" class="url">Vcpkg</a
              >: Microsoft's C++ package manager. Install with:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">cd ~
git clone https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg
./vcpkg/bootstrap-vcpkg.sh
export VCPKG_ROOT=~/vcpkg
export PATH=$VCPKG_ROOT:$PATH</code></pre>
              </div>
              Add the export lines to your .bashrc file to make them permanent.
            </li>
            <li class="bullet">
              <a href="https://conan.io/" class="url">Conan</a>: Alternative C++
              package manager. Install with:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">pip install conan</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          GPU Programming:
          <ul>
            <li class="bullet">
              <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit" class="url"
                >CUDA Toolkit</a
              >: GPU programming framework. Follow the installation instructions
              on the
              <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads" class="url"
                >NVIDIA website</a
              >. After installation, add these lines to your .bashrc:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre><code class="language-bash"># CUDA Toolkit paths
export PATH=/usr/local/cuda-13.1/bin:$PATH
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-13.1/lib64:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH</code></pre>
              </div>
              Replace "13.1" with your installed version. Update the environment:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">source ~/.bashrc</code></pre>
              </div>
              to update the environment variables. Verify the installation by running:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">nvcc --version</code></pre>
              </div>
              <li>
                <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cudnn" class="url"
                  >cuDNN</a
                >: Deep learning library. Follow the instructions on the <a
                  href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cudnn"
                  class="url">NVIDIA cuDNN website</a
                >.
              </li>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            Profiling:
            <ul>
