        <section id="python">
          <h2 class="h3-visual">Python and Anaconda</h2>
          <ul>
            <li class="bullet">
              <a href="https://www.python.org/" class="url">Python</a>: Most
              Linux distributions include Python by default. Check your version:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">python3 --version</code></pre>
              </div>
              To prevent pip from installing packages globally (which helps keep your
              system clean), create a pip configuration file:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">mkdir -p ~/.config/pip
echo "[global]" > ~/.config/pip/pip.conf
echo "user = true" >> ~/.config/pip/pip.conf</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="bullet">
              <a href="https://www.anaconda.com/" class="url">Anaconda</a>:
              Python development and package management platform. Download the
              installer from the
              <a
                href="https://www.anaconda.com/docs/getting-started/anaconda/install#macos-linux-installation:how-do-i-verify-my-installers-integrity"
                class="url">Anaconda website</a
              > and follow the installation instructions. Verify installation:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">source ~/.bashrc
conda --version</code></pre>
              </div>
              Managing your Anaconda environments:
              <ul>
                <li class="bullet">
                  Prevent Auto-Activation: If you don't want the (base)
                  environment to start every time you open a terminal, run:
                  <div
                    class="code-container"
                    style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
                  >
                    <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                    <pre
                      class="command-line"
                      data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">conda config --set auto_activate_base false</code></pre>
                  </div>
                </li>
                <li class="bullet">
                  Create a New Environment: To create a new environment with a
                  specific Python version, run:
                  <div
                    class="code-container"
                    style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
                  >
                    <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                    <pre
                      class="command-line"
                      data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">conda create -n myenv python=3.10</code></pre>
                  </div>
                </li>
                <li class="bullet">
                  Activate an Environment: To activate an environment, run:
                  <div
                    class="code-container"
                    style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
                  >
                    <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                    <pre
                      class="command-line"
                      data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">conda activate myenv</code></pre>
                  </div>
                </li>
                <li class="bullet">
                  Deactivate an Environment: To deactivate the current
                  environment, run:
                  <div
                    class="code-container"
                    style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
                  >
                    <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                    <pre
                      class="command-line"
                      data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">conda deactivate</code></pre>
                  </div>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <strong>Note:</strong> The global pip restriction mentioned earlier
              can interfere with pip usage inside Anaconda environments. To temporarily
              override it, prefix your pip commands with:
              <div
                class="code-container"
                style="text-align: center; margin: 25px auto; max-width: 40em;"
              >
                <button class="copy-btn">Copy</button>
                <pre
                  class="command-line"
                  data-host="pc"><code class="language-bash">PIP_REQUIRE_VIRTUALENV=false</code></pre>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

